ame number of golds, silver medals are used to rank them, and then again by bronze if the total silvers are level.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ranking method has been a point of contention in years gone by, with some countries electing to sort by total medals when the statistics suit them.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American media has oftenpresented the table by total medalsin order to place the USA on top.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2311, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999840513284, \"rank\": 1.4549676955198461e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chinese media tried to claim glory in Tokyo three years ago by adding the medals won by Hong Kong and Taiwan to its tally.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2405, \"end\": 2412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8839317866169112, \"rank\": 0.12985523944975474, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2443, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9960067409771014, \"rank\": 0.004008965132073956, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2493, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.7199525895591388, \"rank\": 0.38894257133391574, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"